figgy.title: Fine-tune bib number match / retrieval for PUO recordings
Replace callnumber queries to OL postgres with OL api queries in RecordingCollector
Numismatics Dashboard doesn't show Numismatics Issues

comments.body:
I believe the course we want to ingest is called `puo`.

Here are the courses without numbers in their titles, and the count of recordings in each:

```
select C.CourseNo, Count(R.idRecording) from Recordings R
  left join Selections S on S.idRecording=R.idRecording 
  left join jSelections jS on S.idSelection=jS.idSelection 
  left join Courses C on jS.idCourse=C.idCourse 
  where CourseNo not like '%[0-9]%'
  group by CourseNo;
```


11 puo recordings have already been ingested into figgy manually: https://figgy.princeton.edu/?f%5Bhuman_readable_type_ssim%5D%5B%5D=Recording&f%5Bpart_of_ssim%5D%5B%5D=PUO&q=

At least one of these is also in the reserves database.

Output of initial run is in deploy home on figgy-staging. file is called `puo_files.txt`

I'm adding the record id to the "Importing [titles]" log message in a forthcoming PR.

figgy.title: BrowseEverything Google Drive ingest is failing for more than a threshold number of items
Updates browse-everything and uses BrowseEverythingIngestJob to recurse through directories selected for upload

comments.body: https://github.com/jrgriffiniii/browse-everything/commit/cc23bce7c26e2e236663a0de8c8fa30d5f629114 and https://github.com/jrgriffiniii/browse-everything/commit/04fdde48bd40f891e178164126f3178815854a08 were needed in order to restore some of the RSpec suites for Rails 6.0.x releases upstream

> A couple of small changes requested.
> 
> I have one question about the background job -- it looks like it uploads the whole directly in one go, rather than spinning off one job per file. is that right? has it always worked that way?

https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/pull/3290/files#diff-de15adcdf347e4ab95f601c96297a7aaL29 and https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/pull/3290/files#diff-c9f03683144c96ae5b9d2636a43218d0L11 indicates that `BrowseEverythingIngestJob` is currently structured to use an array of IDs from the `PendingUpload` resources. I have no objection to changing this within this PR.
@jrgriffiniii I don't think we need to change it in this PR. Thanks for clarifying.

pul_solr.title: Adding a config file for the new library-staging stand alone solr server

comments.body: Hi @carolyncole, I think we may want to consider [reloading the cores](https://github.com/pulibrary/pul_solr/commit/3b3b42ffd85da11781b176a2e53ae2c9bd7693f9#diff-6dc906be0643182e5bae6aa1506221e6) instead on deploys. Let me know if you'd like to try this approach out together. I tried deploying the library-staging role with this branch but the solr service restart failed.
@tampakis I'd be happy to make a change.  Although I believe I just need to rerun the library-staging playbook in ansible to get the restart to work.  I had just run in on library-prod.
@tampakis If you want to try and rerun it now.  I ran the ansible update to allow deploy the ability to restart solr.  If reloading the cores would be better we can do that too.
Works great, I'm +1 with this approach. I think if we ever run into situations in the future where it takes a long time to restart solr we might prefer to reload the cores instead.
